description: The Year One Annuals continue, exploring pivotal events and untold stories of the DC Universe's greatest heroes. Superboy learns from whom he was cloned, and the knowledge may have disastrous long-term effects on his life. Â
name: The Lost Boys

description: The Legends of the Dead Earth Annuals continue. A sun-worshipping medieval society chooses a flying teenager to become the new Superboy, but when he learns that the SuperMAN of that world is corrupt, it falls to him to take down his superior - an act which in itself is a terrible crime.
name: Fathers and Suns

description:
Pulp Heroes, the DCU Annuals event, continues with a story in the spirit of the adventure magazines of the 1930s. A cryptic message from Rex Leech leads Superboy and Roxy to a mysterious island where dinosaurs run free, Rex runs the natives, and Superboy gets to run around in a loincloth when he crowns himself 'King of the Jungle' and fights a giant white gorilla.

3 parts, each with a separate art team.

Follow-up to the 'Blackout' story in the Superman titles, featuring the same island from that storyline. Lola-la and Mr. Z make return appearances.
name: Land of the Lost

description:
Wolverine faces off against a group of pirates on the Island of Telambang.

Wolverine tracks a man that has been missing along with a plane and its crew. A band of pirates kill all the crew save two women. Wolverine finally finds Kojima Noburo, the man he was tracking. The dying man tells Wolverine about the Cult of the Black Blade and the Muramasa Sword. Wolverine kills the pirates. Wolverine travels to Madripoor where he meets up with Lindsay McCabe.
name: Sword Quest

description:
Wolverine is ambushed by Silver Samurai!

Wolverine investigates in Madripoor. Silver Samurai is looking for the Black Blade too. Jessica Drew is possesed by the Black Blade. After fighting Jessica, Wolverine becomes possesed by the Black Blade.
name: Possession In The Law

description:
Wolverine, in the guise of Patch, is under the control of the Muramasa Blade!

Silver Samurai and Lindsay free Wolverine of the Black Blade.
name: ...The Black Blade...

description:
Wolverine fights Roughhouse and Bloodscream on the streets of Madripoor.

Wolverine investigates a murder. Wolverine battles Bloodsport and Roughouse and is defeated. The assassins capture Tyger Tiger.
name: Bloodsport

description:
Wolverine intercepts a drug shipment in the Golden Triangle.

Wolverine battles more pirates.
name: Hunter's Moon!

description:
Logan and Karma throw down with Bloodscream and Roughhouse.

Karma helps Wolverine take down General Coy. Wolverine battles Bloodsport and Roughouse and wins. After finding Jessica Drew, Lindsay McCabe, and Tyger Tiger, Wolverine and crew and surrounded by the Prince and his gaurds.
name: Roughouse!

description:
The Hulk heads to Madripoor!

Mr. Fixit (the Hulk) and Patch (Wolverine) team up.
name: Mr. Fixit Comes To Town

description:
Logan manipulates the Hulk into helping him disrupt the various criminal operations in Madripoor.

Hulk and Wolverine take down some pirates and free women slaves.
name: If It Ain't Broke..!

description:
A group of hunters become Wolverineâs prey in a remote. But why is Logan stalking these men and taking them out one by one?

A group of mercenaries were hired to take hostages in US embassy in Iraq. While holding hostages and waiting for their ransom they raped a Canadian nun. But after a few days special forces took the embassy back. Some of mercenaries could escape.Exactly five years later Wolverine is out to hunt them and to revenge the nun.
name: Promises To Keep

description:
Wolverine gets wrapped up in the memories of the death of Silverfox at the hands of Sabretooth.

It is Wolverine's birthday. He remembers Sabretooth killing Silver Fox on his birthday. The two fought and Sabretooth won.
name: 24 Hours

description:
Wolverine faces off against a legion of vampires!

In a San Francisco museum of antiquities, two vampires are attempting to steal a valuable stone. However, the vampires break the stone and it shatters. In Madripoor, Archie explains to Patch that his crazy brother, Burt, is being declared mentally incompetent. Soon, he is able to convince Patch and Jessica Drew to come to San Francisco with him to help. When they arrive in San Francisco, they find Burt revealing the same stone that was part of the robbery attempt at the museum. Later, Jessica Drew investigates. At Burtâs competency hearing, a horde of vampires crash through the window after Burt.
name: Brother's Keeper

description:
Wolverine steals a police car to chase down Jessica Drew while an army of vampires a squad of vampires pursue him as well.

In the courtroom, Wolverine, Burt Corrigan, and Archie Corrigan are holding their own against a horde of vampire beings. Jessica Drew arrives at the courtroom during mid-brawl and joins the fight. Archie tells Jessica about the Gehenna Stone, and how the followers of Baâal want to assemble it. The master of the vampires orders his minions to continue their pursuit, which will drive them to him, as he has foreseen â along with the reassembled Gehenna Stone.
name: Straits Of San Francisco

description:
Baâal recovers a fragment of the Gehenna Stone!

In California, Burt, Archie, Patch and Jessica are all in a car, discussing the events of the day when they are suddenly pursued by cops, as they are driving a stolen vehicle. However, Patch makes short work of them, after which they again ask Burt what this is all about. Burt proceeds to tell them all about the Gehenna Stone, Baâal, and his followers from ancient times. He tells them of how Baâal was struck down by the Hand of God. Of how Baâalâs spirit was put into a stone, which was then smashed by the Hand of God and tossed all over the world. He also tells them how the pieces of this stone have been turning up, slowly. When asked if they could see the piece of the stone that Burt is carrying, he flips out on them. They arrive at the airport, only to be met by Baâal and his followers. During the melee that ensues, Burt is knocked out and his stone stolen from him. Patch confronts Baâal, but finds that he is no match. After their battle, Baâal leaves on a plane with his followers. Patch and his crew decide to follow him, wherever it may lead them. In Madripoor, twin brothers enter the Princess Bar. They are at each otherâs throats the entire time. They also have a piece of the stone. They rent a room above the Princess Bar from OâDonnell, the bar owner. Up in the room, they continue to fight, to the point where they are killing each other. Down below, OâDonnell sits at a table when a drop of blood drips down from the ceiling. When he goes up to investigate, he notices the brothers are both dead, and the stone is glowing next to them.
name: Blood Ties

description:
Wolverine battles Baâal and his minions aboard an airplane while it hurtles toward the ocean.

Above the Pacific Ocean, Archie, Patch, and Jessica are all in Archieâs plane, chasing after the âvampiresâ in their plane. Patch, realizing that this has gone far enough, goes in the back to change. In the meantime, Archie catches up to the vampire plane, whereupon Jessica leaps onto it. Patch comes out of the back, only this time heâs dressed in his black and tan costume of Wolverine. He also leaps onto the vampire plane to take them down, together with Jessica. In the process, he learns that Jessica was aware of âPatchâsâ identity the whole time. They meet with some resistance but, thanks to Wolverineâs claws, short work is made of them. Up ahead, Burt drops a rope-ladder down towards the vampireâs plane. The vampire plane swerves, knocking Jessica out the door. She grabs hold of a vampire and then makes an attempt to grab onto the ladder Burt that dropped. Instead of Jessica grabbing the ladder, vampires do. They climb up the ladder and, one by one, are taken out by Burt. In the vampire plane, Baâal is admiring his stone, all complete except for one piece, when he is interrupted by one of his followers who tell him about Wolverine. Baâal transforms him into a gorilla-like form. Baâal then proceeds to knock Wolverine around like a toy until they end up in the cabin. Wolverine ducks and the pilot is taken out. Wolverine then takes out the control panel and is able to escape through the roof of the plane. He leaps from the plane and grabs Jessica for the ride. They are able to grab onto the ladder from Archieâs plane as the vampire plane explodes in mid-air. As it does, Wolverine gets an ominous sign from Baâal that he is getting stronger, and soon... unstoppable. In Madripoor, OâDonnell is questioned by the police about the brotherâs murder. He shows the cop and Lindsay McCabe the stone that he holds proudly. Lindsay is drawn to the stone and, later that night, she goes to OâDonnellâs room so that she can see it. They end up in a passionate embrace until the door is busted down. The aide to the prince of Madripoor has heard that OâDonnell has something of interest to him, and he wants it now!
name: Flying Wolves

description:
Wolverine seeks out Prince Baran to recover the Gehenna Stone.

In the streets of Madripoor, Wolverine saves Lindsay McCabe from Chief Tai and his men. When he asks Tai what that was all about, he gets nowhere. He then decides that, for answers, he needs to go to the Princess Bar. When he gets there, he finds OâDonnell and Lindsay in a huge fight. After Lindsay storms out, Patch and OâDonnell discuss the goings-on of the past events. Patch laments about the fact that his âsecretâ identity is no longer very secret when Archie storms in, angry at Wolverine for not letting him toss Burt out of the plane when he had a chance. Wolverine calms the situation down while OâDonnell tells them about the stone and how it was taken from him by the Princeâs aid, Johann. Just then, they are interrupted by Chief Tai and his men. A huge brawl breaks out until Wolverine pins Tai up against the wall and gets everybody to calm down. At that point, Wolverine starts to put the pieces together of what is going on. Turns out, that each piece of the stone makes people crazy, except him â heâs already nasty. Thatâs a bad sign, as the Prince of Madripoor has the last piece. They need to head up to the princeâs castle and defuse the situation. On the streets of Madripoor, Burt meets up with some followers of Baâal. They have taken a prostitute and are going to make her a sacrifice. Burt fights for her safety, until he is subdued. Just when it looks the worse, Jessica Drew shows up and takes out two of the three vampires with gunshots. The third vampire takes off with Jessica and Burt in pursuit. When the vampire finally gets to his destination, Jessica recognizes it as the princeâs castle. She enters the castle so she can warn the prince about the impending danger When she gets to his chamberâs, the prince introduces her to his guest, Baâal!!!!
name: Homecoming

description:
This is it! The final confrontation between Baâal and Wolverine!

On the way to the princeâs castle, Archie Corrigan, Captain Tai, Patch (in his Madripoor disguise of Wolverine) and OâDonnell are ambushed by the followers of Baâal. Patch tricks the vampires into dragging him into the woods, where he can dispose of them quickly, and separate from the group so he can make it to the castle quicker. In the castle, Jessica Drew is trying to explain to the Prince of Madripoor how dangerous his âguest,â Baâal, is. However, the prince disbelieves her story, especially once Baâal offers the prince immortality in payment of the last gem. In the streets of Madripoor, Burt is doing all he can to figure out where Jessica has gone. After one of the residents of Madripoor tells him that the prince knows all, Burt makes his way over there directly. Back in the castle, the Prince has decided that he will make his decision tomorrow. Baâal doesnât like that and tells him that he has to make a decision now. The prince loses his temper and orders Baâal out of the castle. Baâal resists and is surrounded by Johann and the princeâs guards. Baâal knows where the gem is hiding and shoves his hand into Johannâs throat, pulling the final piece out!! A melee then breaks out between Baâalâs followers and the princeâs guards. At that very moment, Wolverine shows up and starts to make his way through all of the âvampires.â He makes it to Baâal, who has now put the last gem into the stone. He now has ultimate power and, with it, transforms all of his followers into real vampires. As Jessica and the prince battle with Baâalâs followers, Wolverine and Baâal tangle in an epic struggle. Baâal is able to gain the upper hand and is just about to deliver the final blow to Wolverine, when Burt shows up and knocks the stone out of Baâalâs hand. In the race to get the stone, Baâal wins, but Wolverine summons an inner, spiritual strength to counterâs Baâalâs evil and is able to slash the stone into a million pieces. He then stabs Baâal in the gut, as they tumble through the palace wall into the surrounding water. When they land, Ba'al is dead.
name: Electric Warriors

deck: Klaus Janson and John Byrne take over the artwork in atmospheric Madripoor, as a new, cybernetic crime boss is in town with a lethal batch of heroin.
description: Wolverine uses his hyper-senses to detect cocaine shipments in Madripoor! Which villain is behind this dangerous drug ring? Logan intends to find outâ¦
name: Basics!

description:
President Guillermo Caridad of Tierra Verde wants to create his own super heroesâ¦using uniquely laced drugs!

Wolverine goes to rescue Roughouse, and finds that crime boss Geist is holding him captive for experimentation.
name: All At Sea

description:
Â¡Viva la revoluciÃ³n! Cuban mutant La Bandera overthrows Tierra Verdeâs drug ring! Meanwhile, Wolverine must save Roughouse from an overdose.

Wolverine travels to Puerto Verde, capital city of Tierra Verde. Spotting Tiger Shark fighting a young lady, he intervenes to help her. Tiger Shark runs off. Wolverine continues on to meet an old acquaintance: CIA agent Jack Bascomb. Jack tells him all about the lady he just rescued: La Bandera. She has connections through her father to Fidel Castro's revolution in Cuba. In New York, Kingpin and President Caridad discuss Tiger Shark's presence in Tierra Verde. The Kingpin then goes to meet Doctor Doom, Magneto and the Red Skull. The president of Tierra Verde back home again, learns from his scientists about a new, powerful version of cocaine. Wolverine seeks help from Sister Salvation and then attacks Geist to get information that will lead him to Roughhouse. La Bandera and her followers attack the palace while Geist leads Wolverine down to the lower levels of the palace. Tiger Shark attacks again and drags Wolverine under the water. Wolverine escapes ocean but, before he can make it up to the surface, he is dragged under again by Tiger Shark.
name: Heroes & Villains

description:
Does Wolverine stand a chance fighting Tiger Shark in his own waters? Meanwhile, Sister Salvation tests out her mutant strength on the rapidly weakening Roughouse.

Tiger Shark battles Wolverine under the water. Needing to get away, Tiger Shark traps Wolverine by shoving his adamantium claws into a coral reef. Wolverine struggles to free himself while Tiger Shark takes off. Tiger Shark goes to the Tierra Verde medical center and with Geist accosts La Bandera. La Bandera manages to escape but Tiger Shark is on her tail, only for Wolverine to intercept him and knock him off a railing. At that same time, Sister Salvation heals Roughhouse, but only so he can be drugged up again. Wolverine and La Bandera find Roughhouse and free him and then head to the roof to get to their escape route: a helicopter. Wolverine, Roughhouse, Sister Salvation and La Bandera take off in the helicopter, but as soon as it's over the ocean, it is attacked by Tiger Shark, who leaps from the ocean into the air. Tiger Shark is thrown off into a school of sharks below. Roughhouse starts to recover, but Wolverine unknowingly has been shot by one of Geistâs cocaine darts...
name: Miracles

description:
Sister Salvation harbors a secret. Wolverine spirals into hallucinatory mania after being drugged with experimental, and very dangerous, cocaine. This is one trip from which Logan canât escape!

Wolverine, La Bandera, and Roughouse have escaped with Sister Salvation.

But the cocaine has kicked in and Wolverine must battle against the Beast within his mind and body, and the Beast has a name...The Spore.
name: Battleground

description:
Sister Salvation uses her healing powers to conquer Spore! But at what cost to her own health? Meanwhile, Logan uncovers a horrifying connection between Geist and the C.I.A.

The Spore has taken of Presidente Caridad and is looking to grow, only Wolverine, La Bandera and her rebel army stand in the way.

But how can they stop a disease that only a Celestial previously destroyed? Sister Salvation may hold the key in her hand.

Meanwhile, Geist's past finally catches up with him.
name: Endings

description:
A street urchin has stolen the briefcase of the Snow Queen- and itâs packed to kill! Can Logan come between the assassin and the young boy before the streets of Madripoor go up in smoke?

The Snow Queen is in Madripoor but before she can take of business one of Madripoor's street urchins steals her briefcase. Unfortunately for the kid, he stole an assassin's briefcase, and she values that briefcase more than that kid's life.

Now it is up to Wolverine to find the kid and get the Snow Queen her briefcase back before she does it herself.
name: Snow Blind

description:
Logan discovers an old friend has been killed, and his home ransacked! Will Wolverine win back Bando Saburoâs most prized possession from a gaggle of thugs?

Logan once found peace and beauty in the house of his friend Bando Saburo.

But greed and pride have destroyed what Logan once found in that house in Japan.

Wolverine now looks for those responsible, and to ask whether what they did was worth it?
name: Memory Of Peace

description:
Jessica Drew, Spider-Woman, uncovers the Lazarus Project, an evil plot to destroy a small city!

Prince Baran of Madripoor and General Nguyen Ngoc Coy, one of Madripoor's two crimelords, are meeting with Mr. Andover about their future endeavors.

The future involves the mysterious Lazerus Project, and the key to the project, The Master Form.
name: The Lazarus Project Part 1 of 4 - Predators And Prey!

description:
Logan has a serious case of amnesia! And the safety of an entire town waits in the crossfire! Karma catches wind of her uncleâs plans to destroy Rumika.

After his fight with the Pinocchio Robot, Wolverine washes up on the island of Rumika, off the coast of Madripoor. He has no memory of who he is or why he is there.

The people of Rumika accept this stranger into their village, and Wolverine starts to find peace again without his past to haunt him. Little does he know that the people of Rumika have been chosen to protect the Master Form from anyone who would try to take it.

Still there is something in the air, a smell, that is familiar but Wolverine's can not identify.
name: The Lazarus Project Part 2 of 4 - The Stranger

description: Target, Karma and Logan share their backstories in a brief heart-to-heartâ¦just before an attack is launched against them!
name: The Lazarus Project Part 3 of 4 - The Road Back

description: Wolverine, Karma and Target confront the goons behind the Lazarus Project!
name: The Lazarus Project Part 4 of 4 - Family Matters

description: The Yakuza wants Wolverine's head. Wolverine defeats Goro's men.
name: Killing Zone

description: Wolverine is recovering from his last battle. Goro stabs Wolverine with his sword and seems to die. Wolverine sees Jean but she sends him back.
name: Terminal Trauma

description: Believing Him to be dead, the Yakuza bury Wolverine. Wolverine wakes up and breaks out of his grave and is pretty ticked off. Wolverine finds the Yakuza and kills them all.
name: Grave Undertakings

description: Wolverine is in the woods and encounters the Hunter in the Darkness.
name: The Hunter In Darkness

description: Wolverine visits his old buddy, Puck. Lady Deathstrike is tracking Wolverine. Gateway sends Deathstrike, Wolverine, and Puck back-in-time to the Spanish Civil War.
name: Blood And Claws! Part 1 of 3 - Blood, Sand and Claws!

description: Wolverine fights in the Spanish Civil War.
name: Blood And Claws! Part 2 of 3 - ...It Tolls For Thee!

description: Wolverine battles Deathstrike. Donald Pierce has a plan to take out Wolverine for good, with two androids: Albert and Elsie Dee.
name: Blood And Claws! Part 3 of 3 - Fall Back & Spring Forward

description: Wolverine saves Elsie Dee from a fire. Elsie Dee warns Wolverine that she was programmed to kill him. Together, they disengage the bomb.
name: Deconstruction

description: Forge studies Elsie Dee. Albert upgrades himself and plans to kill Wolverine and rescue Elsie Dee. Albert frees himself of is programming and sacrifices himself.
name: Reconstruction

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
After the stealth bomber, which was hijacked by the Android Albert, crashed, Wolverine finds himself in the sewers seriously injured. While Elsie-Dee tries to find help, Wolverine is attacked by a rejuvenated Sabretooth. At the same time, Masque redirects the flood through the tunnel where Wolverine and Sabretooth fight. Albert, who was believed dead, climbs out of the bomber.

Note: Includes a two-page art piece by Mike Mignola and a one-pager by Art Thibert.

Synopsis

A stealth bomber has just crashed in a river. It's passengers: Wolverine, Elsie-Dee, and Albert. The latter two are androids charged with killing Wolverine. It seems at least one of the androids has switched sides, as Forge and Jubilee find, upon searching the wreckage, that Wolverine and Elsie-Dee ejected before the crash. Back on the surface, a rescue crew pulls the two mutants aboard but holds little hope for finding the missing friend, especially since a storm is rolling in and has the potential to flood the river and sewage areas. Jubilee and Forge promise each other that they won't stop looking for Wolverine.

On the river bank, Else-Dee sees that she can't scale the steep walls to the city. She continues to pull an airline seat to a sewage drain, pries the bars open, and lugs Wolverine's unconscious body within the protection of the sewers. He's out cold; his body healing. Elsie-Dee runs for some help. As she leaves, Wolverine wakes up with the memory of Silver Fox fresh in his mind. He stumbles around the sewers in a stupor, questioning why his lady had to die. Elsie-Dee runs into a tunnel with floating bodies, most of them alligators with their throats ripped out. She continues on and rambles about getting help for Wolverine. One of the figures rises. It's Sabretooth. As Wolverine continues to wander, he recalls what killed his precious Silver Fox: it was Sabretooth. Wolverine wants revenge.

Topside, Forge makes a phone call to some people who may have a better chance at locating Wolverine. Jubilee fumes that the duo isn't doing enough.

Down below, Masque and his rag-tag band of Morlocks fears that the rains will flood their home. Masque collects two big men and directs them to redirect the flow of the flood waters.

As Wolverine continues to wander, he shifts between consciousness in the sewers and in the past when confronting Sabretooth about Silver Fox's death. Sabretooth, being able to sense Wolverine, joins in the conversation. The two ultimately meet and begin a royal brawl. As the ultimate way to get into Wolverine's head, Sabretooth claims to be his father. Wolverine won't believe it and the two continue their ferocious clash. Down another tunnel, Elsie-Dee literally runs into Cable. She tells him her friend needs help. Cable appears intrigued.

Back at the clash, Wolverine and Sabretooth are interrupted by a deluge of sewer vermin. Rats and alligators rush by, quickly followed by a gush of water, fueled by Masque's redirection of the river. The two men instinctively continue fighting as they are washed down the sewers. Wolverine finds an opening off to the side and crawls inside, hoping that Sabretooth simply gets sucked down stream. No such luck, as the beast claws his way after Wolverine. In front of Wolverine is a large, locked, metal door. Behind is Sabretooth. Behind Sabretooth is a grate that the Morlocks have just lowered. Trapped, the two men continue their fight with Sabretooth still claiming parentage. On the other side of the door, Cable and Elsie-Dee hear the fight. She begs him to help Wolverine get out.

Topside, Forge and Jubilee wait. At the bottom of the river, Albert is reanimated. He must find Elsie-Dee.
name: Down In The Bottoms

description:
Wolverine and Sabretooth continue their battle, even through a flooding of the sewers. Cable and Elsie Dee manage to pitch Wolverine from the frying pan and into the fire. SHIELD fortunately shows up and pulls everyone to safety. Sabretooth's claim at parentage is questioned and answered.

Synopsis

Wolverine is trapped in the sewers with a locked metal door on one side and a recently lowered steel grate on the other. To make matters worse, Sabretooth (claiming parental rights), is trapped with him. Even worse, the sewers are flooded and this small space is no exception. Further, Sabretooth, despite the few minutes the two men have left, is intent on killing Wolverine. Wolverine's one last hope belongs to the man called Cable, who stands on the opposite side of the locked door. He and Elsie-Dee hear the fight. She wants Cable to blow the lock off the door, but Cable is reluctant since there is a flooded corridor behind the door. Also, he doesn't really like Wolverine, so there's that. Not content, Elsie-Dee tries to take Cable's gun by force. He knocks her away. She removes her head and chucks it at Cable's, effectively knocking him down. Her body seizes the chance and grabs the gun. She then shoots as best as a headless body can and finally hits the lock on the door. Cable was right, there was a lot of water behind that door. The water sweeps the four people down the sewers and Sabretooth gets taken by an undercurrent. Elsie-Dee reattaches her head in time for the group to run into a grate that collects the garbage. They are stuck and escape looks hopeless.

On the streets above, Forge tells Jubilee that his friend should be arriving soon to help them search for Wolverine. Jubilee pauses when she hears screaming from the sewers. Forge tells her it's only Morlocks. The Morlocks, it seems, are trapped, as the grate that Cable and Co. are trapped in is becoming to obstructed to allow water to pass through; the Morlocks could drown if the grate isn't cleared. Masque orders the manual override to be hit to clean the grate.

At the grate, Cable wants to shoot Elsie-Dee, as it is her fault they are in this mess. Wolverine severs the gun as Sabretooth leaps from the garbage and renews his attack. Just then, however, the Morlocks succeed in flipping the switch for the grate cleaner. Seeing no other option, Elsie-Dee squeezes through the grate-works and finds the gears. Having separated her bomb circuitry, she detaches her head and throws it back into the fray. Her body blows up and destroys the gears, allowing the three men and Elsie-Dee's head to continue down the sewers. Masque orders all the water to flow uninhibited to the East River.

Jubilee finally learns who Forge has been waiting for: Nick Fury. In a rescue chopper above the East River, the S.H.I.E.L.D. crew picks up the heat signatures of three bodies coming out of the sewers. Wolverine and Cable are pulled aboard and a warning is given to make sure Sabretooth is out cold before pulling him in to the chopper. As the craft flies away, Cable throws the head of Elsie-Dee to Wolverine. He's relieved, but she tells him that her main batteries and recharging capabilities were in her body. She only has minutes left. Wolverine is upset and Sabretooth, who was not properly sedated, lunges towards his professed son out of sheer disgust. He tries to rip Wolverine's throat out but Elsie-Dee attacks first. She bites his neck and propels Sabretooth out of the chopper. Cable and company rescue Wolverine before he goes over to save Elsie-Dee. She and Sabretooth crash into the river.

As the helicopter continues on, Wolverine comes to grips with Elsie-Dee's parting. When asked who Sabretooth was, he explains that he was supposedly his father. A worker states that there is no way the two are related based on blood work that had recently been done. When Wolverine states that Sabretooth was lying, Nick Fury claims that Sabretooth actually did believe he was Wolverine's father. But any further info on the subject was classified.

In the river, Elsie-Dee continues her assault on Sabretooth. He yanks her off his neck and attempts to smash her. Her eyes go blank and it looks as if Sabretooth will crush her until Albert cuts Sabretooth and takes Elsie-Dee to a power source. She boots back up and recognizes Albert.
name: Papa Was A Rolling Stone!

description:
Needing to clear his head, Wolverine jumps out of the S.H.I.E.L.D. helicopter and runs wild through Central Park. He then stops by the zoo and finds a disturbed young man torturing animals. After teaching the guy a lesson, Wolverine continues his personal journey. Elsewhere, Lady Yuriko searches for Wolverine. As she passes over a bridge, Sabretooth emerges with a renewed desire to find his "son," Wolverine.

Note: Includes an art piece by the team of Marc Silvestri and Dan Green.
name: Under The Skin

description: Aboard a cruise ship, Wolverine battles a nameless demon who is murdering pregnant mothers, one of which may be the future mother of a telepath.
name: Babes At Sea

description: The Hunter in the Darkness is captured and put on show. Wolverine thinks something will gone down. Albert is in the Morlock tunnels and fixes Elsie Dee. Wolverine with the help of Jubilee, fight Sabretooth, Lady Deathstrike, and the Hunter in the Darkness.
name: Claws Over Times Square!

description: Wolverine battles Sabretooth and Deathstrike. Wolverine has Weapon X flashbacks.
name: Home Is The Hunter...

description:
Teen angst runs high as Wolverine tries to subdue a teenaged gunman from hurting anyone, including himself!

description:
Wolverine, Mystique, and Spiral confront Mojo to save not only Jubilee, but the entire universe!

It's the end of time itself, the Big Crunch. Which would usually lead to the Big Bang except Mojo is intefering. Now it's up to Wolverine, Mystique, Spiral and Jubilee to save, well, everything that is and everything that will be. But Wolverine is being pursued across what is left by demonic energy beings, Spiral and Mystique are pretty much lost in the past and Jubilee is leashed to Mojo's walking chair. It's all up to her and her love for Wolverine to save the space-time- continium.

description:
As mass murder Cletus Kassidy is being taken taken to Seattle to have his symbiote removed from his blood, he manages to use his filed down tooth to draw enough blood to form his symbiote and begins a battle with the Guardsmen in his mobile transport. He then kills the accompanying scientist and prepares to kill the escorting officers, but is confronted by Spider-Man who has followed to assure he doesn't escape. He unfortunately is forced to let him go when his thermocanon is destroyed and is forced to decide between saving the injured officers or his pursuit, deciding to save their lives and tagging his escaping police car with a spider-tracer.Carnage then ditches the police car much to Spider-Man's frustration, while Carnage tracks down his first friend Billy, to murder him and set up a new pattern for himself.Spider-Man fortunately uses his spider-sense to find and save him from Carnage, with the two renewing their fight in a lumber mill. They battle until Spider-Man is thrown into a barrel of resin impeding his speed, as Carnage prepares to kill the wall crawler, however Billy returns to stop his former friend. However he is prepared to be killed with Carnage removing his symbiote to prove it's him who wants to kill his friend, with Cletus hen being knocked out by Spider-Man.Carnage is then imprisoned in the Vault, in a microwave generator cell to stop his symbiote, while he decides not to try and escape to continue to be unpredictable.

In the Eastside, Cloak and Dagger infiltrate and begin taking down a drug refining plant, as Dagger wonders what has brought about Cloak's highly aggressive actions. However when confronted by more armed men Cloak teleports them out as he fears for her safety, even though he refuses to admit it. They then return to finish the cartel,but Cloak's anxiety to protect Dagger nearly leads to the death of innocent bystanders who are only saved by Dagger. Seeing this he flees to the Holy Ghost Church with Dagger eventually finding him, and Cloak admitting what's bothered him.

As the powerless Joe Smith rides through New York's subway on his way to work at the Children's Center, however upon arriving he finds it has been robbed with all the equipment taken or destroyed.He then decides he must be a hero and clean up his neighborhood, and dons his old costume. He quickly ends up in a fight with three thugs, and as they prepare to kill him the crowd of onlookers inspired chases the gang off.

In the Manhattan apartment of the Rhino's mother and niece the three arrive to find they have been robbed, with his niece finding the locket her mother had given her has been stolen. He then makes her a promise to retrieve it,he then suits up and heads for a shady bar,and retrieving the locket.As he returns the locket he also brings enough money to bring about the rest of their family.however his furious mother throws him from the apartment for his stealing.
name: Carnage is Back

description:
In part two of this four-part arc, Peter and Ben are confused when the skeleton dug up from the bottom of the smokestack (very old plot point from years back) turns out to be a clone. What?

Ben and Peter discuss what the results of the skeleton might mean as they return from the Avengers' headquarters. Both begin to question what the new discovery means about who/what they are.

Meanwhile, Carnage's symbiote has indeed escaped, though without his host (Cletus Kassidy). After several pages of fighting with Spider-man and anyone else who gets in his way, the symbiote leaves its current host body and bonds with Ben, forming a sort of "Spider-Carnage."

However, the Carnage situation seems to take a back seat in this issue (despite taking up most of the story) when Peter goes to see Seward Trainer in the hospital. Seward refuses to see him--because of a phone call he receives just as Peter is entering the hospital. The man on the other end of the phone call? A mysterious, shadowed figure in a car just outside the hospital. In just one short page, the clone saga has suddenly taken a whole new direction.
name: Web of Carnage, Part 2 of 4:  And Now -- Spider Carnage
